        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Iran's new supreme leader's first statement: Takeaways, optics, messaging Middle East Issued on: 12/03/2026 - 15:28 Modified: 12/03/2026 - 15:29 In his first message since he was appointed Iran's new supreme leader, Ayatollah Mojtaba Khamenei ordered the vital Strait of Hormuz oil shipping lane to remain closed and called on Gulf Arab states to \"shut down\" US bases. It was a message of defiance and continuity, explains FRANCE 24's Leela Jacinto. Two votes, two standards: UN resolutions on Iran war underscores diplomatic dilemmas 12/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon: Israeli strikes Beirut in new 'lage-scale' attack 12/03/2026 Middle East Iran's new Supreme Leader Mojtaba Khamenei has 'very good links with the IRGC' 12/03/2026 Middle East Mojtaba Khamenei as Iran's new Supreme Leader signals continuity to international community 12/03/2026 Middle East Middle East war: Oil tankers set ablaze in the Gulf in latest Iranian attacks 12/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran: 'An American war in desperate search of a strategy', expert says 12/03/2026 Middle East Banking, finance and consultancy firms evacuate staff in Gulf States 11/03/2026 Middle East 'Two decades in the making': Expert details how Mossad built its spy network in Iran 11/03/2026 Middle East US war on Iran: Using military force to achieve political outcomes rarely produces lasting stability 11/03/2026 Middle East"
